For foreign investors with non-USD liabilities, if they perceive there will be a weaker USD in the future, even flat US equity prices will deliver negative returns. Parts of the Mag7 have declined substantially but $AAPL is biggest left to tumble.

Obviously US agriculture is a major target for other countries but I believe the Tech giants are an equally appealing target for retaliation. European investors lose money holding $AAPL if the $USD currency declines. Selling US assets is a logical move. US is no longer a true ally 😞.

$AAPL is such a high weight in all the major indices that a selloff will inherently bring down the larger market averages. It has traded with an inverse correlation to $SPY and $QQQ recently but that is a quirk of trading strategies IMO.  Fascinating case to watch and speculate on.

$AAPL trades with the PE of a growth company but they have not delivered growth in the past few years and they don't have a credible growth story. A consumer recessions is not a great time to sell $1,000 phones. I can't predict the short term but the trapdoor is set for a substantial correction.
